About the job
As a Junior Software Developer you contribute together with an agile development team to the translation of process data into usable system information combined with a great frontend. While the energy transition is gaining momentum we keep growing at Locamation. Whitin the current challenges on the energy systems, together we ensure that our customers gain insight into their data regarding the energy networks and consumption. Do you want to contribute and develop the best software to do so? This might be the job for you!

Nowadays, increasingly higher demands are being placed on our energy grid. We believe there is a need for a different approach to substation automation. One that uses less equipment and less manhours to implement and maintain. One that generates data on which operators can balance and protect their highly dynamic grids.

Our current first generation centralized solutions are running at Ellevio, National Grid, Liander and many more companies. We are now in the process of creating a whole new product line with new sensors and new software. As our products are part of our society’s vital infrastructure, the pressure is on quality, real-time data handling, a seamless combination with our hardware and on industry standards.

Tasks & Responsibilities

Develop and improve software for our virtualized substation server and DevOps;
Translate the different needs from our customers into development solutions;
Development of the software architecture, together with the team;
Ensuring cyber security (secure coding principles, OWASP, PEN tests, etc.).

Locamation

High-quality, reliable and real-time data is essential for enabling advanced applications and maximum utilization of actual grid capacity. At Locamation we provide insight and predictability based on real-time data as the first step to information-driven grid management. Our speciality is the acquisition and processing of time-critical, high-quality data from substations. We are working on a sustainable future regarding the energy system and are growing. Will you grow and develop together with us?

What’s in it for you?
The opportunity to directly impact on the energy transition at an ambitious organization that is funded by Alliander, a company that also holds the largest Distribution Systems Operator (DSO) in the Netherlands;
An inspiring environment of a compact team, working on a combination of software and sensors in the heart of the electricity grid;
An international oriented, human-centric, and inclusive company culture where you can have a direct impact;
The opportunity to interact with our international clients and partners;
An nice place to work together with super smart, fun, creative colleagues and a fast and dynamic work environment;
A strong benefits package:
A yearly salary between €42.000,- & €55.000,-;
Annually you’ll get 25 days off;
On top of that, Locamation will grant you five additional days per year to be with your family and friends, e.g. between Christmas and New Years;
The possibility to work from home or remote. Every Monday we all come together at the office;
Pension scheme;
Travel allowance.


Desired Skills and Experience
What do you bring along?

A Bachelor degree, preferably in Computer Science or Electrical Engineering;
Experience with JavaScript, Python, C, C++, DevOps, Linux;
Knowledge and awareness of Secure Programming;
Excellent communication skills in English (at Locamation we communicate in both Dutch and English);
The ambition and willingness to travel occasionally to (international) partners or clients for workshops and demonstrations.

Don’t you tick all the boxes above? Please feel free to apply anyway because your ambition and motivation might be just as important as your experience.

NOTE: This position is only open to those permitted to work in the Netherlands.

Apply!

We would love to get to know you. Send your resume to Björn Bogerd, Recruiter at Locamation. You will receive a response within a few business days and hear whether and when a first digital interview will be scheduled. Do you have any questions in advance? Contact Björn via +31(0)6-48709874 or send an e-mail: bjorn.bogerd@locamation.com.

Do you want to know more about who we are and what we do? Check www.locamation.com for more information.

Good to know: we are exploring the possibility of entering an office in the Arnhem/Apeldoorn region

About the job
Job description
We invite you to join our strong team of developers, which already includes over 30 people. You'll be able to collaborate with other professionals working in front-end, back-end, data collection, data engineering and data scientists working on artificial intelligence.

What you'll do with us:
You'll develop a mobile app for effortless car control - lightning-fast refuelling, one-click insurance, maintenance reminders and much more;
You'll develop other products based on a variety of vehicle data - TOP SECRET - which we're only talking about internally for now. You will be one of the first to contribute to innovation;
You will use best practices in new product design and development - you will have the freedom to propose and apply the latest technologies.
Job requirements
What we expect from you:
At least 1-2 years of experience working with React Native;
Practical React Native skills;
You make productive use of React's capabilities, and are able to apply modern practices such as React Hooks;
Strategic Thinking;
Native experience (Obj-C/Swift for iOS or Java/Kotlin for Android) is a big advantage;
Ability to take responsibility;
Willingness to improve the product;
Ability to develop the highest level of quality standards;
Self-driven development of priorities;
We offer:
A friendly and supportive team;
A dynamic work culture and the possibility to work fully or partially remotely (we have spacious offices in Vilnius and Kaunas);
Career development programmes - we fund various professional trainings;
Unlimited paid holidays;
Team building events;
Company values you can be truly proud of;
Employee incentive and bonus programmes;
Supplementary health insurance.
Sallary gross from 3000 EUR.

About the job
We are looking for a Data Scientist for an international project of a European Union agency (EU).

Ideal candidates should have:

University degree with at least 3 years of experience in data science OR non-university degree with at least 5 years of experience in data science;
At least three years of experience during the past five years in evaluating and optimising large complex data sets and existing outputs; Data quality assurance; automating data flows and output production; Data linkage;
Advanced R, in particular creating outputs and dashboards using Markdown and Shiny;
Knowledge or professional expertise in Python;

Responsabilities

Work closely with epidemiologists, disease experts and other ECDC staff in developing and maintaining technical solutions for automated surveillance data analysis and visualisation;
Strengthen existing surveillance data models, flows and routine outputs through state-ofthe-art technology, optimising integration, automation and user-friendliness while complying with scientific standards and best practice;
Identify, assess, validate, and support data linkage with, external large databases to enhance routine surveillance, help to answer specific public health questions and support public health decision-making;
Create, maintain and refine automated surveillance processes and outputs including surveillance and situational awareness dashboards in the context of early threat detection, assessment and response planning;
Support relevant IT projects by ensuring that data requirements are properly defined;

Company

Being part of THEWHITEAM is to collaborate with a company formed by professionals with extensive experience in technology consulting.

We firmly believe that companies and clients mark the way forward in the sector, but this is built by people. We consider it vitally important that our organisation is based on our best asset and value-added brand, which is our team.

Benefits

On the other hand, I also leave you a small summary of the company's policies so that you can get to know us a little better:

Our agreement is that of Consultancy and market research companies.
We have 23 days holiday a year
The company gives us the day of our birthday as a gift, so that we can enjoy it without working.
We have 14 payments, 12 monthly and two extra ones (June and December).
As flexible remuneration we can ask for a childcare voucher and also medical + dental insurance.

